  "body": "## Issue\r\n\r\nRight now, Truffle Dashboard just connects to whatever network the user has set with MetaMask. To accommodate this, we define the special-purpose `\"dashboard\"` network as a `truffle-config.js` default, defining `network_id` with the normally dangerous `\"*\"` (which we compensate for via Dashboard web UI warning messages for mainnet and alerts when switching networks).\r\n\r\nThis new behavior makes Truffle Dashboard extremely useful for public testnet development/deployment as well as provides a familiar experience for mainnet.\r\n\r\nBut wallets like MetaMask define APIs for adding custom networks and switching between networks! Truffle Dashboard should be expanded to add functionality around this, namely to allow users to use the Dashboard web UI to easily switch some or all of the following:\r\n- Networks defined in truffle-config\r\n- Common public networks (maybe this can be user-config defined?)\r\n- Browser-running Ganache (like heck yeah)\r\nThe priority of these probably varies, or at least perhaps we can later consider these issues separately.\r\n\r\nNote an open question remains here regarding the user experience with Truffle– or Ganache–managed networks, since MetaMask brings its own accounts that would be in conflict with the accounts provided by these managed networks. Further research and requirement gathering seems warranted here.\r\n",
